  <span id="freeText3876661943104829359" style="display:none">My first contact with the story of Sinuhe was through the old Holywood movie The Egyptian from 1954, as a big admirer of the old cinema, when i saw the story that was put in Ancient Egypt and in time of mystical pharaoh Akhenaten the movie finished in my watchlist, the movie is nothing special but i was intrigued by the story, i found that the story was written by Finnish author Mika Waltari, i found the book in local bookstore, and the magic started, the book is ofcourse ten times better than the movie, it is interesting and really transports you to that ancient time, you can really feel all the characters, places and scenes from the book, the book is really great adventure but also the book touches deeper themes about social system, war, politics, human relations, religion. I really recommend this book to anyone who is interested in Ancient Egypt and Ancient Civilizations and great adventure. My grade 5/5.</span>
